# Clinical Trial Dossier
**Document Ref:** AERA-RD-CLIN-2025

**Department:** Research & Development

**Status:** Certified Medical Research Record

## 1. Trial Executive Overview
*This dossier compiles the clinical data gathered during the FY2025 multi-center trials evaluating the efficacy of AERA’s upcycled peptide and Bakuchiol formulations.*

Testing was conducted in collaboration with independent dermatological institutes in Athens, Greece, and Seoul, South Korea.

## 2. Methodology & Cohort Profile
Total Human Subjects: 450 healthy adult participants across diverse age brackets and genders.

Dosing Protocol: Topical application of the test concentrate twice daily over a continuous 28-day window.

Exclusion Criteria: Complete exclusion of any animal-tested control elements, strictly upholding AERA's global cruelty-free mandate.

## 3. Empirical Results & Dermal Efficacy Indices
Skin Barrier Recovery: 94.2% of participants demonstrated a statistically significant reduction in Trans-Epidermal Water Loss (TEWL) within a 14-day window.

Cellular Turnover Acceleration: In vitro testing confirmed a 40% improvement in structural collagen matrix synthesis when exposed to our upcycled peptide variations.

Adverse Reaction Index: 0.0% cases of chemical contact dermatitis, localized erythema, or photo-sensitivity were recorded during the testing period.

